{"dataset":"articles","provider":"pursuit","banner_url":null,"id":"110620","text":"<div data-component=\"Tier3Hero\" ><div id=\"parallax-section-undefined\" class=\"parallax-component\" data-v-47405038><div id=\"background-media-undefined\" class=\"background-media\" data-v-47405038><video id=\"video-undefined\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0015/110742/vlcsnap-2024-07-04-14h19m20s517.png\" data-v-47405038><source src=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/video_file/0018/110628/vecteezy_passengers-on-the-metro-station-time-lapse_28392104.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\" data-v-47405038></video></div><div class=\"textbox-list\" data-v-47405038><!--[--><div id=\"textbox-0-undefined\" class=\"textbox textbox--center\" data-v-47405038><div class=\"textbox-content\" id=\"textbox-content-0-undefined\" data-v-47405038><p>Melbourne cannot afford to lag behind its global peers. Other major cities have successfully implemented comprehensive night-time transport systems that cater to both the entertainment crowd and essential workers.</p></div></div><div id=\"textbox-1-undefined\" class=\"textbox textbox--center\" data-v-47405038><div class=\"textbox-content\" id=\"textbox-content-1-undefined\" data-v-47405038><p>For instance, cities like <a href=\"https://new.mta.info/guides/riding-the-subway#:~:text=The subway operates 24 hours,the subway fare is $2.90.\" target=\"_self\">New York</a> and <a href=\"https://tfl.gov.uk/campaign/tube-improvements/what-we-are-doing/night-tube\" target=\"_self\">London</a> have extensive 24-hour public transport networks that serve as models for Melbourne’s ambitions.</p></div></div><div id=\"textbox-2-undefined\" class=\"textbox textbox--center\" data-v-47405038><div class=\"textbox-content\" id=\"textbox-content-2-undefined\" data-v-47405038><p>Ensuring safe and reliable transport for night-time workers and continuing to fill the gaps in the network are essential for the success of Melbourne’s 24-hour city vision.</p></div></div><!--]--></div></div></div><p><span class=\"underline\"><em><a href=\"https://www.unimelb.edu.au/cities/projects/current-projects/map-of-the-month\" target=\"_self\">Map of the Month</a></em></span><em> is a science communication project of the University of Melbourne (</em><span class=\"underline\"><em><a href=\"https://www.unimelb.edu.au/cities\" target=\"_self\">Melbourne Centre for Cities</a></em></span><em>, </em><span class=\"underline\"><em><a href=\"https://aurin.org.au/\" target=\"_self\">AURIN</a></em></span><em>, </em><span class=\"underline\"><em><a href=\"https://www.unimelb.edu.au/mdap\" target=\"_self\">Melbourne Data Analytics Platform</a></em></span><em> and </em><span class=\"underline\"><em><a href=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/\" target=\"_self\">Pursuit</a></em></span><em>) using maps to spark important policy conversations across metropolitan Melbourne. This pilot is supported by the </em><span class=\"underline\"><em><a href=\"https://www.lmcf.org.au/\" target=\"_self\">Lord Mayor’s Charitable Foundation</a></em></span><em> and in partnership with the </em><span class=\"underline\"><em><a href=\"https://www.suburbandevelopment.vic.gov.au/suburban-revitalisation\" target=\"_self\">Victorian Office for Suburban Development</a></em></span><em> and the </em><span class=\"underline\"><em><a href=\"https://www.mav.asn.au/\" target=\"_self\">Municipal Association of Victoria</a></em></span><em>. Academics, community leaders and government representatives from across Melbourne contribute to the maps and accompanying stories.</em></p><p class=\"left\"><em>This month’s story was produced in collaboration with the Australian Research Council </em><span class=\"underline\"><em><a href=\"https://www.unimelb.edu.au/cities/projects/current-projects/night-shift\" target=\"_self\">'Night Shift' project</a></em></span><em>, and the maps were produced by </em><em><a href=\"https://findanexpert.unimelb.edu.au/profile/672545-stuart-lee\" target=\"_self\">Dr Stuart Lee</a></em><em>, Flavia Barar and Max Stevens using data from </em><em><a href=\"https://www.ptv.vic.gov.au/footer/data-and-reporting/datasets/\" target=\"_self\">Public Transport Victoria</a></em><em>.</em><em><br /></em><em><br /></em><em>*not their real name.</em></p>\n<p>This article was first published on <a href=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au\">Pursuit</a>. <a href=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/articles/is-melbourne-really-a-24-hr-city-if-public-transport-stops\">Read the original article.</a></p>","date_published":"2024-07-04T00:00:00+10:00","date_updated":"2024-07-04T00:00:00+10:00","url":"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/articles/is-melbourne-really-a-24-hr-city-if-public-transport-stops","title":"Is Melbourne really a 24-hour city if public transport stops?","summary":"Sometimes Melbourne’s public transport goes dark. Our Map of the Month shows it makes life hard – even dangerous – for those in our night-time economy","org_objects":[],"tag_objects":[],"author_objects":[{"name":"Anna Edwards","url":"https:\\/\\/pursuit.unimelb.edu.au\\/individuals\\/anna-edwards","orcid":"","fae_url":"https://findanexpert.unimelb.edu.au/profile/888062-anna-edwards","email":""},{"name":"Professor Michele Acuto","url":"https:\\/\\/pursuit.unimelb.edu.au\\/individuals\\/professor-michele-acuto","orcid":"","fae_url":"https://findanexpert.unimelb.edu.au/profile/823504-michele-acuto","email":""}],"citation_objects":[{"credentials":"Anna Edwards"},{"credentials":"Professor Michele Acuto"}]}